body:
Three bugs identified in code review, plus a missing test annotation.

## Fixes

### Resource leak — `JsonPropertySourceFactory`
`resource.getReader()` was passed directly to Jackson without ever closing the `Reader`. Wrapped in try-with-resources.

```java
try (Reader reader = resource.getReader()) {
    Map source = objectMapper.readValue(reader, LinkedHashMap.class);
    return new MapPropertySource(name, source);
}
```

### Silent exception swallowing — `WebRequestUtils.parseContentType`
`InvalidMediaTypeException` was caught with an empty body, making failures invisible. Added a `Logger` (consistent with the rest of the module) and logs at DEBUG level with the offending content-type value. Also hoisted `contentTypeValue` out of the try block to avoid a redundant call in the catch.

### ThreadLocal memory leak — `RequestPredicateKind.parseRequestPredicate`
`requestPredicateThreadLocal.remove()` was called inline after the loop, so any exception thrown during predicate building would leave the ThreadLocal populated on the pooled thread. Wrapped in try-finally to guarantee cleanup.

```java
requestPredicateThreadLocal.set(requestPredicates);
try {
    // build predicates...
} finally {
    requestPredicateThreadLocal.remove();
}
```

## Test

Added `@SpringLoggingTest` to `WebRequestUtilsTest`, enabling TRACE/INFO/ERROR logging level cycling per test method via the JUnit Jupiter extension.
